Notionally, the effect of the guide magnetic field is noticeable if the Larmor radius in the guide magnetic field is less or equal to the bounce width in the reconnecting magnetic field component. The electron bounce width in the reconnecting magnetic field component Bx is given by (Biskamp and Schindler 1971) 
