Hesse et al. (1999) investigated the effect of different electron masses on the collisionless dissipation process in the reconnection region for anti-parallel configurations. The target of the investigation was to study whether different physics in the diffusion region might lead to different dissipation, thereby influencing and potentially changing the larger scale behavior of the system under investigation. Hesse et al. approximated the reconnection electric field using bounce widths defined above: 
